10. LESSONS LEARNED
Technical
ARM architecture matters — armhf (32-bit) vs arm64 (64-bit) are not interchangeable. Pi 5 requires arm64
Generic dev boards have limitations dedicated hardware does not — CP210x serial instability under load is real
Trixie/Bookworm GPG key handling changed — apt-key is deprecated, sqv is the new verifier
Streaming serial output needs threading, not sequential read/write
Boot order on Pi 5 is USB-first by default — always insert SD card before USB devices at power-on
Strategic
Know when to stop and why. Four days on Marauder taught everything needed to document and deprioritize it intelligently
Post-goal drift is real. After Security+, the compulsion to keep pushing produced diminishing returns. Recognizing it is the fix
Workspace organization directly impacts troubleshooting efficiency. A clean lab reduces friction
Every wall hit in this build is more valuable portfolio material than a smooth tutorial follow-along would have been
